            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "In https://www.chromium.org/Home/chromium-security/ssca the Chromium developers advise web applications to enable SameSite cookies whenever possible to mitigate Spectre.\r\n\r\n> If that is merged it will make more sense to add support for it here.\r\n\r\nSupport for SameSite cookies landed in Werkzeug in https://github.com/pallets/werkzeug/pull/1167 and was released in Werkzeug 0.14.0.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/pallets/flask/blob/master/docs/security.rst#set-cookie-options says SameSite cookies are not supported by Flask yet. It seems there is no longer an open issue to track adding this support. Make sense to reopen this issue to track this? It's useful to have an open issue that users can subscribe to who want to find out when support has landed. Maybe also change \"same-site\" to \"SameSite\" in the issue title since currently searching this repo for \"samesite\" doesn't turn up this issue.\r\n\r\n/cc @davidism @mitsuhiko @untitaker @DasIch et al."
        },
